Pin Functionality
mcu » apollo330P

Detailed Description

Purpose: This is a generated file that provides the function select (FUNCSEL) information for all GPIO pins on Apollo510 devices. It maps each pin to its available functions and is used by the HAL for pin configuration and multiplexing. Do not modify this file directly; regenerate it using the provided script if updates are needed.

Key Features

  1. Complete Pin Mapping: Lists all available functions for every GPIO pin.
  2. Auto-Generated: Maintained by a script to ensure accuracy and consistency.
  3. Multiplexing Support: Enables flexible pin function selection.
  4. Integration: Used by HAL and board support code for pin configuration.
  5. Documentation: Provides a reference for developers configuring pins.

Functionality

  • Map each GPIO pin to its available functions
  • Support pin multiplexing and alternate function selection
  • Serve as a reference for HAL pin configuration routines
  • Enable automated updates via script regeneration

Usage

  1. Use this file as a reference for available pin functions
  2. Configure pins in application or board support code using HAL APIs
  3. Regenerate this file using the generate_funcsel.py script if pin definitions change

Configuration

  • Scripted Generation: Use ambiqsuite/scripts/apollo5/generate_funcsel.py
  • Pin Definitions: Update pin definitions in the script as needed
  • Integration: Ensure this file is included in HAL and board builds
